    "Hence, the HF machinery introduced in Section 3.3 can be straightforwardly repurposed here, if we 'boost' the k argument of the form factors and the one-body terms (which can either come from the kinetic energy or the interaction scheme).",
    "In the periodic gauge that we use here, this operation is straightforward, and can be separately implemented before the HF self-consistent procedure 60.",
    "Wavefunctions in the Boosted and Unboosted FramesThe assumption of a single-q spiral order allowed us to go to a boosted frame in which the HF projector is diagonal in momentum space, viz.",
    "Pk,k ′ ∝ δ k,k ′.",
